posts.title: Elon Musk, H1Bs as a red herring, and the true employment apocalypse coming down the pike: AI   (Long Post / Discussion)
posts.content:
First a note about Elon Musk.

Elon Musk is a "transhumanist" whose main aspiration in life is to see the technological singularity realized for the human race. Put all other things in this context right now, and his actions will make sense, and you will also know when to be skeptical of him.

He is definitively NOT a Christian, and NOT an American. He sides with Trump supporters in the culture wars because he is pro-free speech, anti-censorship and he is anti-Trans and gender ideology.

The former (free speech) because TRUE scientific and philosophical advancement require open, reasoned discourse. Censored or otherwise stunted discourse do not move us forward, they move us backwards.

The latter (gender bullshit), not for any religious reasons, but I suspect merely because it's fucking gross and stupid and as an intelligent guy he can't abide the Orwellian perversion of the lexicon inflicted by gender (and race) theory. Attacking the lexicon with stuff like "men can get pregnant" makes language less meaningful, and as a result, true open discourse less productive, because we waste time quibbling over the literal meaning of words instead of higher concepts.

Now, on the topic of H1Bs. Remember, Elon Musk is THE richest plutocrat in the world. His behavior should shock nobody. But the H1B issue is something of a red herring. The real threat coming down the pike is NOT Indians coming over to work tech jobs.

The real threat is that AI is going to eliminate tens of millions of American jobs in the next decade or so, and they will never come back.

First of all, the majority of those H1B tech or engineering or administrative or Quality jobs are going bye bye. If your job is primarily to sit in meetings, write reports, approve documents, produce data, etc., AI can do ALL of that. The technology isn't there just yet but it will be soon, and then the only barrier will be the regulations.

Depending on the industry, there are almost always a set of governing federal regulations that as of now still require actual human signatories on documents and so forth. That will change eventually, and AI will practically overnight make 10s of millions of people redundant and unemployable, because they've become so specialized in their careers.

It won't just be in tech. Think pharma, finance, healthcare, education. ANY industry that is heavy with administrative personnel. ANY job that does not require your physical body to be somewhere, interact with something, and so forth.

If your job can be done remotely, then AI can do it. Stupid COVID leftists dug their own grave here by insisting all their white collar jobs can be done from home (or on the beach). In fact the COVID shutdown went a long way towards identifying entire organizations within large corporations that are good candidates to be replaced by AI.

So while everyone is yapping about H1B Pajeets taking your jobs, remember the jobs they are being brought here to do aren't going to be around much longer anyways, and we don't have an economic model for what the hell to do with a 25-50% unemployment rate. And this is coming SOONER THAN YOU THINK.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nJnbqG_eQ-w

In that link Musk is talking about Universal Basic Income.

I have no idea how you make something like that work. Where the hell money comes from to just pay out to people for free.

The only thing I can envision is the revival of a sort of colonial economic model, where the USA is such an economic powerhouse, producer of goods and culture for export, as well as natural resources for export, that we become so rich via tariffs and are able to pay out a UBI to the citizenry similar to the way oil rich countries like Saudi Arabia pay their citizens what basically amounts to a UBI derived from oil dividends

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Citizen%27s_Account_Program_(Saudi_Arabia)#:~:text=Through%20the%20programme%2C%20citizens%20in,monthly%20payments%20from%20the%20state.

Anyways. Resist the urge to get angry here. You're looking at the ground in front of you rather than the horizon. All that WEF shit about "you'll own nothing and be happy", has not gone away. When AI takes a chainsaw to the white collar workforce, the people will be BEGGING for a UBI and government benefits, and this society wide change is gonna happen fast, fast, fast, just like COVID did.
